-- Hynix Shares Rise on Report Creditors Ask LG to Run, Take Over Chipmaker
-- Kyung Bok Cho
-- 2010-07-19T00:10:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-19/hynix-shares-rise-on-report-creditors-ask-lg-to-run-take-over-chipmaker.html

          
          
             Hynix Semiconductor Inc. rose in
Seoul trading after the Seoul Economic Daily reported the
chipmaker’s creditors asked LG Group to operate and then take
over the company.  
 The world’s second-largest computer-memory maker gained 1.7
percent to 23,900 won as of 9:09 a.m. on the Korea Exchange. The
benchmark Kospi stock index lost 0.8 percent.  
          
          


  


        